summary:
I'm an Electronic Engineer, with more than 10 experience years in the automation industry.
I have worked at several customers from many countries providing technical support in the automation area.

I joined to Tetra Pak as Field service Engineer Junior after in February 2014, after 3 years I got a promotion as Service Engineer B and afterwards I certified in USA to perform calibrations and FDA validations process for the same company. I have high skills to work under pressure giving support to clients of my best way, also I have been leader several times to carry out projects for the company.
 
Before joining to Tetra Pak I worked at the Mechanic industry area and I have knowledge in types of machines since CNCs until plastic injectors, also I have knowledge in electrostatic painting equipment and I'm able to read any electrical drawing understanding automatism systems.

I have worked with different kind of PLC such as  Ge-Fanuc, Rockwell, Siemens, Pluto, etc, Furthermore I have a wide range knowledge industry in general.
